               <msContents>
                  <summary>

                    <locus target="#153v"/>: colophon mentioning the scribe, Takla Maryam, and belonging to Head priest, Gabra Masqal.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="5r" to="157v" facs="005"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2701Dawit"/>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><locus from="5r" to="125r" facs="005"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>The spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters are not given.  The sections are numbered, the letter is all that is written.</note>
                  <note><ref type="work" corresp="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151"/> has all four plusses that make up the long version</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="125v" to="137r" facs="126"/><title type="complete" ref= "LIT1828Mahale"/>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note><title type="complete" ref="LIT2257salota#Hannah"/> is Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophet</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3"><locus from="137r" to="144r" facs="137"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2362Songof"></title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>In the common version</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4"><locus from="144v" to="153r" facs="145"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2509Weddas">, arranged for the days of the week</title>
